The paper discusses the performance of deep neural networks on visual classification tasks, specifically on the ImageNet and MNIST datasets. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the ability of DNNs to classify images with high confidence, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of evolutionary algorithms and gradient ascent also suggests a connection to neural networks (cs.NE) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
